<p>Use <code>hatching</code> utility classes to apply a diagonal striped
pattern using a single color across light and dark modes. This pattern
uses a <code>135deg</code> repeating-linear-gradient.</p>
<h3 id="class-patterns">Class Patterns</h3>
<table>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 37%" />
<col style="width: 62%" />
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr class="header">
<th>Class Pattern</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code>.hatching-[color]</code></td>
<td>Sets the hatching color for both light and dark modes</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code>.hatching-[color]-[shade]</code></td>
<td>Sets the hatching color shade
(e.g. <code>hatching-blue-400</code>)</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td><code>.light\:hatching-[color]-[shade]</code></td>
<td>Sets the hatching color for <strong>light mode only</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><code>.dark\:hatching-[color]-[shade]</code></td>
<td>Sets the hatching color for <strong>dark mode only</strong></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
